# Development Menu for @web Service

A comprehensive menu of development patterns to aid in LLM-driven feature implementation automation.

## Available Development Patterns

When implementing features, choose from these established patterns based on your needs:

### **Core Building Blocks**
- [Forms](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/forms.mdc) - Form creation, validation, and submission patterns
- [Components](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/components.mdc) - Reusable UI component patterns
- [API Routes](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/api-routes.mdc) - Backend API endpoint patterns
- [Page Routes](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/page-routes.mdc) - Frontend route and page patterns

### **UI & UX Patterns**
- [Tables](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/tables.mdc) - Data display and pagination patterns
- [Layouts](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/layouts.mdc) - Page layout and structure patterns
- [Navigation](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/navigation.mdc) - Navigation and routing patterns
- [Buttons & Actions](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/buttons-actions.mdc) - Interactive element patterns

### **Data & State**
- [Database Integration](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/database.mdc) - Database query and transaction patterns
- [Authentication](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/authentication.mdc) - User authentication and session patterns
- [Validation](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/validation.mdc) - Data validation and error handling patterns
- [Resources](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/resources.mdc) - Generalized dashboard pages with GraphQL integration

### **Infrastructure**
- [Server Setup](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/server.mdc) - Server configuration and middleware patterns
- [File Handling](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/file-handling.mdc) - File upload and processing patterns
- [Email & Notifications](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/email-notifications.mdc) - Communication patterns

### **Testing & Quality**
- [Testing Patterns](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/testing.mdc) - Unit and integration testing patterns
- [Error Handling](mdc:.cursor/rules/menu/error-handling.mdc) - Error boundaries and recovery patterns

## Usage Instructions

1. **Feature Planning**: Review relevant menu items when planning feature implementation
2. **Pattern Selection**: Choose the most appropriate patterns for your specific feature needs
3. **Implementation**: Follow the detailed guidelines in each menu item
4. **Testing**: Use testing patterns to ensure quality
5. **Integration**: Ensure proper integration with existing systems

## Quality Standards

All patterns follow these principles:
- TypeScript-first development
- Accessibility compliance
- Mobile-responsive design
- Performance optimization
- Security best practices
- Maintainable code structure
